---
const stack = [
  "Cursor",
  "Claude Code",
  "Claude API",
  "n8n",
  "Cloudflare Pages",
  "Cloudflare Functions",
  "Docker",
  "Home Assistant",
  "TypeScript",
  "Auth0",
  "REST APIs",
];
---

<section id="about" class="px-6 py-20 border-t border-line">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <p class="font-mono text-sm text-terracotta-deep uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">
      About
    </p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-ink leading-tight">
          I bridge product thinking with hands-on building.
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-body leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            For the last decade I've worked across product management,
            integrations, and platform architecture — at companies like
            Happeo (B2B SaaS, 500+ enterprise clients) and a Unicorn B2B
            SaaS where I led a company-wide Auth0 integration across
            10+ teams.
          </p>
          <p>
            But what I love most is the building. Shipping
            <a
              href="https://cvroast.dev"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-terracotta-deep underline decoration-2 underline-offset-2 hover:decoration-4 transition-all"
            >cvroast.dev</a> with Claude API and Cloudflare. Coordinating
            an open-source community to scale it. Automating a
            40-sensor home with my husband. Helping thousands of people
            navigate tech careers through Tech Immigrants.
          </p>
          <p>
            I work where product, AI, automation, and community
            overlap. That's the lane.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">
            Stack & Tools
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            {
              stack.map((item) => (
                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-cream border border-line rounded-full text-sm text-ink">
                  {item}
                </span>
              ))
            }
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">
            Recent Recognition
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-body">
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta-deep">▸</span>
              ITU Young Innovator Competition Winner (2014)
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta-deep">▸</span>
              Canada Startup Visa (2019)
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="text-terracotta-deep">▸</span>
              50K+ followers across YouTube and Telegram
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
